cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.MA, cs.DS, cs.PL 

This paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category as it deals with the application of argumentation semantics to a logic system, which is a common topic in AI research. It could also belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category as it deals with a specific logic system, prioritised default logic. The paper's focus on structured argumentation and distributed reasoning suggests it could also belong to the Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) sub-category. The use of game proof theories could place it in the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category, while the use of a framework for structured argumentation could place it in the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category.
